items.sentence: Do you think Tom would be able do that by himself?
Tom cleared his throat before he started speaking.
I jog through Central Park every morning at 6 a.m.
I felt like singing loudly when the exam was over.
I don't know what's in store for me in the future.
I had my suitcase carried to my room by a bellboy.
I used to drop in at the bookstore on my way home.
I put in an hour of jogging before I go to school.
I think you made up that story about the accident.
I want to see baseball on television this evening.
